From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 23:10:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: omap-mcbsp: derive CLKGDV from fclk for simple-audio-card

When the McBSP is the bit/frame-clock master and the machine driver only
describes the codec MCLK ratio (e.g. simple-audio-card's mclk-fs) without
ever calling snd_soc_dai_set_clkdiv(), the driver left CLKGDV at 0 -- so the
bit clock was the *undivided* functional clock -- and sized the I2S frame as
in_freq/rate BCLKs.  On the Google Nexus Q (steelhead) McBSP2 -> TAS5713 link
(fclk = 24.576 MHz) that produced BCLK = 24.576 MHz and a 256-BCLK frame,
i.e. FSYNC = 96 kHz for a 48 kHz stream -- audio played back exactly twice
too fast (a 207 s track drained in ~100 s, so librespot auto-skipped ~40 s in).

The factory kernel's dedicated machine driver set both set_sysclk(fclk) and
set_clkdiv(CLKGDV = fclk / (32 * rate)).  Reproduce that without requiring
every simple-audio-card board to grow a set_clkdiv() call: when the McBSP is
master and no explicit clk_div was supplied, derive CLKGDV from the real
functional-clock rate and use a minimal wlen*channels I2S frame.  This yields
CLKGDV = 15 (BCLK 1.536 MHz), a 32-BCLK frame and FSYNC = 48 kHz -- bit
identical to stock.  Boards that do call set_clkdiv keep their behaviour.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 sound/soc/ti/omap-mcbsp.c | 36 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 30 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/ti/omap-mcbsp.c b/sound/soc/ti/omap-mcbsp.c
--- a/sound/soc/ti/omap-mcbsp.c
+++ b/sound/soc/ti/omap-mcbsp.c
@@ -1029,13 +1029,37 @@
 	 * by _counting_ BCLKs. Calculate frame size in BCLKs */
 	master = mcbsp->fmt & SND_SOC_DAIFMT_CLOCK_PROVIDER_MASK;
 	if (master == SND_SOC_DAIFMT_BP_FP) {
-		div = mcbsp->clk_div ? mcbsp->clk_div : 1;
-		framesize = (mcbsp->in_freq / div) / params_rate(params);
+		unsigned int fclk_rate = mcbsp->clk_div ?
+					 0 : clk_get_rate(mcbsp->fclk);
 
-		if (framesize < wlen * channels) {
-			printk(KERN_ERR "%s: not enough bandwidth for desired rate and "
-					"channels\n", __func__);
-			return -EINVAL;
+		if (fclk_rate) {
+			/*
+			 * The machine driver only described the MCLK ratio
+			 * (e.g. simple-audio-card's mclk-fs) and never called
+			 * set_clkdiv(), so clk_div is unset.  The SRG is sourced
+			 * from the McBSP functional clock, so derive the bit
+			 * clock divider (CLKGDV) from the *real* fclk and use a
+			 * minimal I2S frame (wlen * channels).  Without this the
+			 * bit clock would be the undivided fclk and the frame
+			 * would be in_freq/rate BCLKs long, so FSYNC would come
+			 * out at the wrong rate (2x on steelhead's 24.576 MHz
+			 * McBSP2 -> TAS5713 link).
+			 */
+			framesize = wlen * channels;
+			div = fclk_rate / (framesize * params_rate(params));
+			if (!div)
+				div = 1;
+			regs->srgr1	&= ~CLKGDV(0xff);
+			regs->srgr1	|= CLKGDV(div - 1);
+		} else {
+			div = mcbsp->clk_div ? mcbsp->clk_div : 1;
+			framesize = (mcbsp->in_freq / div) / params_rate(params);
+
+			if (framesize < wlen * channels) {
+				printk(KERN_ERR "%s: not enough bandwidth for desired rate and "
+						"channels\n", __func__);
+				return -EINVAL;
+			}
 		}
 	} else
 		framesize = wlen * channels;
